{
  "stem": "10181.3",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That was the first major thing what I noticed.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Of course, like I said, the Germans were there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And once in a while, I don't know where they went to, but there were big convoys going through, you know, the army convoys on-- on the main road.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But this was only real sign of the war, but there were other things too.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There were the nightly air raids, which started to get worse in '41, '42.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The British used to bomb at night, and the Americans by day.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I knew that even then.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "You know.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The British liked to fly at night.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The Americans didn't like to fly at night.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "This I didn't know at the time, but I knew the British flew at night and the Americans by day because-- I found this out because the planes got shot down, you know, and that's how I found out who-- who was who.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Our little village, Dinxperlo, was right on the border.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was almost cut in half by big barbed wire.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "On the other side was a German-- little German village, and it was the beginning of the [? rural ?] area, OK?",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Heavy industrialized area, which in '41, '42 was a main target of the Allies.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And apparently, the way it used to-- they-- they used to sort of assemble above us.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They used to come from England, the airplanes, and used to assemble in-- not just above us, but in a general area and then continue.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They came from three different directions apparently, and at the same time, this also was-- the Germans came from the-- from-- from their own air fields and tried to shoot the planes down.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Plus, there was anti-aircraft guns in the area too.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Heavy, very heavy.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
